# ─── Linear ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required. Used to poll issues and (optionally) post progress comments.
# Generate at: https://linear.app/settings/api → Personal API keys
LINEAR_API_KEY=lin_api_...

# ─── PostHog (error-tracking reports → Linear tickets) ────────────────────────
# Optional. Used by the `posthog:` watcher (and the `symphony-posthog` CLI) to
# pull error-tracking reports and file a Linear ticket for each new one.
# POSTHOG_PERSONAL_API_KEY must be a *personal* API key (starts with `phx_`),
# generated at: <host>/settings/user-api-keys — a `phc_` project key only
# writes events and cannot read reports.
# POSTHOG_HOST=https://us.posthog.com
# POSTHOG_PROJECT_ID=49303
# POSTHOG_PERSONAL_API_KEY=phx_...

# ─── Firebase function logs (error scan → Linear tickets) ─────────────────────
# Optional. Used by the `firebase_logs:` watcher (and the `symphony-firebase-logs`
# CLI) to scan Cloud Function logs for errors and file a Linear ticket for each
# new fixable one. Reads logs via the `gcloud` CLI, which must be authenticated
# with Logs Viewer access to the project (`gcloud auth login` / a service account).
# The project id defaults to firebase_logs.project_id → query_insights.project_id
# in WORKFLOW.md; these env vars are only a fallback when neither is set.
# GCLOUD_PROJECT=team-dsc-au
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=team-dsc-au

# ─── Claude / Anthropic ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional. If set, Claude Code uses this key instead of OAuth.
# Obtain at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# If omitted, run `claude` once and use /login to authenticate via browser OAuth.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# ─── Claude model routing ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# CLAUDE_MODEL controls which model is used for each agent run.
#   "auto"            — Symphony asks Haiku to classify each task and picks
#                       the cheapest model that can handle it. Requires
#                       ANTHROPIC_API_KEY to be set; falls back to Sonnet if not.
#   any model name    — always use that exact model (skips Haiku classification).
#
# RECOMMENDED: pin Opus. "auto" only reserves Opus for architecture/migrations/
# greenfield, so ordinary tickets run on Haiku/Sonnet — weaker than a direct
# `claude` desktop session. Pin Opus to match that quality; switch to "auto"
# only when cost matters more than resolution quality.
CLAUDE_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8
#
# Override individual tier model names (e.g. to pin to a specific snapshot):
# CLAUDE_HAIKU_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# CLAUDE_SONNET_MODEL=claude-sonnet-5
# CLAUDE_OPUS_MODEL=claude-opus-4-8

# ─── Codex fallback ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When Claude is rate-limited or unavailable, Symphony will try the Codex CLI
# next (if installed: brew install codex). No API key required — Codex handles
# its own auth. Set CODEX_ENDPOINT only if routing through a proxy or Azure.
#
# CODEX_ENDPOINT=https://api.openai.com/v1   # optional proxy / Azure override

# ─── Local LLM fallback (via codex exec --oss) ───────────────────────────────
# Last-resort fallback. Runs `codex exec --oss --local-provider <LOCAL_LLM_PROVIDER>`,
# optionally with `-m <LOCAL_LLM_MODEL>`. No API key needed — codex connects to
# the local Ollama (or LM Studio) server directly.
#
# LOCAL_LLM_PROVIDER=ollama          # or: lmstudio
# LOCAL_LLM_MODEL=qwen3.5:9b         # optional: specific model tag to use

# ---- Slack credentials for completion notifications and bot interactions ----
# Set these to enable Slack notifications when tasks complete
# SLACK_COMPLETION_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/...
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-...

# ─── MCP server API keys (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Symphony's agent-mcp.json wires up the SuperClaude_Framework MCP server set
# (https://github.com/SuperClaude-Org/SuperClaude_Framework). Five of the eight
# servers need no key (playwright, sequential-thinking, context7, serena,
# chrome-devtools). The remaining three pick up the keys below; if a key is
# unset the server starts but its tools return auth errors at call time.
#
# Tavily — web search & real-time info retrieval. Get key from https://app.tavily.com
# TAVILY_API_KEY=tvly-...
#
# Magic (21st.dev) — modern UI component generation. Get key from https://21st.dev
# TWENTYFIRST_API_KEY=...
#
# Morphllm Fast Apply — context-aware code modifications. Get key from https://morphllm.com
# MORPH_API_KEY=...
